entry.title: [ios] Create MagicStackCollectionViewController
entry.content:
This is a UICollectionView implementation of the Magic Stack using

a DiffableDataSource. MagicStackLayoutConfigurator manages the

compositional layout for this UICollectionView. EditButtonConfig/Cell

represent the edit button at the end of the Magic Stack and is its own

NSCollectionLayoutSection after the section containing the cards.



The one change in experience between the layout is that when focusing

a middle module, there is no longer peeking on both sides, only the

right. The default behavior was difficult to achieve since the

UICollectionView will not render cells outside of its bounds, so by

following the current layoutGuide for the Magic Stack, the module would

be too narrow if we wanted to make enough space for the left and

right module to be rendered. This could be rectified later by making

the moduleLayoutGuide wider for this implementation.

entry.title: [Cert Provisioning] Destroy cert scheduler on service shutdown
entry.content:
Previously, cert provisioning keyed service did not have shutdown and

was destroying itself with destructor and not Shutdown. The cert service

depends on invalidation service which is destroyed on Shutdown and

expects its dependants to do the same.



For example, invalidation service expects InvalidationHandlers

to unregister before the service is shutdown, thus handlers must

unregister on Shutdown. Before this change, cert invalidators were

unregistering on destruction, which happens after shutdown and were

breaking order and causing crashes.



Now, the whole cert provisioning stack is destroyed on service shutdown

before service destruction.



CertProvisioningAsh uses the service and outlives it, as it was before,

without any breaks.

entry.title: [Protected Audiences] Deflake some InterestGroupBrowserTests.
entry.content:
navigator.runAdAuction() has default script timeouts of 50 ms. This is

not long enough on memory bots (and timing may be a bit tight on debug

builds, too, or even on release bots). This CL migrates simpler

InterestGroupBrowserTests that call navigator.runAdAuction() directly

to using RunAuctionAndWait() and RunAuctionAndWaitForUrl().



"Simpler" in this context means tests that call EvalJs with a function

that only calls "await navigator.runAdAuction({...})", with no extra

Javascript, as the RunAuctionAndWait() family of methods only take the

"{...}" value as an argument, and no additional JS.



This CL also updates RunAuctionAndNavigateFencedFrame() to increase

timeouts just like RunAuctionAndWait() does, though perhaps they should

be updated to use a shared helper.



More complicated tests will be fixed in followup CLs.

entry.title: view-transition: Fix rendering of elements with clip-path on descendants
entry.content:
The visual overflow rect computation code in ViewTransition assumes that

if an element has a clip-path, its content will be sized to the bounds

of that clip-path. The clip-path extent can be larger than the contents

of that element.



The above assumption is only true if the element with the clip-path is

layerized. Otherwise the size of the overflow is an intersection of the

element's painted content with the clip-path. This leads to incorrect

overflow calculation for an element's overflow rect when its not

layerized.



Fix the above by forcing layerization on descendants of a named element

if it has a clip-path. This is easier than knowing whether the content

will be layerized by the paint step later.

entry.title: [Autofill] Call SetPreventHighlightingOfAutofilledFields() on all fields
entry.content:
The purpose of SetPreventHighlightingOfAutofilledFields() is during

a preview to "lowlight" the fields that have already been autofilled,

so that the previewed fields stand out.



Before this CL, this only applied to the fields of the form that was

currently being previewed.



The general motivation is lowlighting the fields of the current

form but not those outside of the current form might confuse the

user, especially since the boundaries of forms don't have to

matche what the user perceives as a form.



The concrete motivation is to unblock crrev.com/c/5321681, which

decouples form_util::ApplyFormFields() from a form, which in turn

is necessary for preview to work in some cases with multiple forms in

an iframe.

entry.title: Allow access() of render nodes in video decoding sandbox for Intel/AMD.
entry.content:
A libdrm patch landed that makes drmGetMinorType() call access() with

node paths [1]. drmGetMinorType() is called from drmGetNodeTypeFromFd()

which is called by libva during initialization.



Before this CL, access() was not allowed for the hardware video decoding

sandbox on ChromeOS. Because of that our Lacros and OOPVD tests broke

when the libdrm patch mentioned above landed. This CL allows doing

access() through the broker process on the sysfs paths corresponding to

the render nodes and (on AMD) /dev/dri.



Note that this is still fine with respect to making sure that the

hardware video decoding sandbox is at least as tight as the GPU process

sandbox. For Intel/AMD, the GPU process pre-sandbox also allows

COMMAND_ACCESS [2].

entry.title: [iOS] Remove -setPrimary: from BVC.
entry.content:
The -setPrimary: method on the BVC does two things.



- It forces the BVC's broadcast state to update.

- It logs that the BVC was made primary/not-primary in the tab usage

recorder.



Updating the broadcast state is unnecessary, since the broadcast state

is computed from other properties, and changing the primacy of the BVC

doesn't change these properties.



The tab usage recorder update is a model layer change that can be moved

out of the BVC, since any code with access to a BVC pointer has access

to the backbone container needed to fetch the tab usage recorder.



This CL removes -setPrimary: from the BVC and from BrowserInterface.



-setPrimary was only called through the BrowserInterface in two places

(MainController and SceneController). It was never called internally in

the BVC.



These two calls are replaced by updates to TabUsageRecorderBrowserAgent.

entry.title: [//cc/slim] Hardcode //cc/slim to use GL_TEXTURE_2D as texture target
entry.content:
//cc/slim currently computes the texture target that it passes to

TransferableResource::MakeGpu() by calling

ClientSharedImage::GetTextureTarget(SCANOUT). This logic dates back to

the introduction of this class [1], where it presumably originally came

from here [2]. However, in [2] the texture target is hardcoded to

GL_TEXTURE_2D unless the resource is an overlay candidate, which it

never is in this case (`is_overlay_candidate` is hardcoded to false).

Hence, GL_TEXTURE_2D should always be used here. It *will* in fact

always be used due to the SharedImageFormat in question being one that

will never be in the exception list for needing a platform-specific

texture target (explained in detail here [3]), and hence

ClientSharedImage::GetTextureTarget() returning GL_TEXTURE_2D [4].



This CL hardcodes this use case to use GL_TEXTURE_2D with an explanatory

comment for clarity.

entry.title: Add permissions .well-known endpoint for Protected Audience API WPTs.
entry.content:
This .well-known is fetched at the origin of the interest group's owner,

and specifies as a URL parameter the origin of frame that's attempting

to join or leave that interest group.



This is implemented such that the origin of the frame is ignored

altogether, and the determination of which operations are allowed

depends strictly on the origin of the interest group owner, and

specifically on the subdomain of the origin of the interest group owner.

wptserve serves each of its two domains at both the raw domain and each

of five subdomains.



- www: disallows both join and leave

- www1: allows join, but not leave

- www2: allows leave, but not join

- 天気の良い日 / élève: allow both join and leave

- anything else (including no subdomain): returns a 404



More information about the permissions endpoint can be found at:

https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE.md#13-permission-delegation



This change depends on

https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/pull/44398

to be usable from web platform tests.

entry.title: [bookmarks] Avoid passing BookmarkModel in observer APIs
entry.content:
Including a pointer to BookmarkModel in BookmarkModelObserver APIs is

somewhat redundant, as observers usually know what they are observing.

They often do so by either maintaining a pointer to BookmarkModel

directly or because they use a ScopedObservation (which also exposes

BookmarkModel via ScopedObservation::GetSource()).



In addition to being redundant, it is error-prone for ongoing efforts

(see linked bug) that reuse BookmarkModelObserver when dealing with

abstractions that expose a transformed or limited view of an underlying

BookmarkModel instance. This is the case for

sync_bookmarks::BookmarkModelView, which benefits directly in this patch

as it is obvious in the changes to class

sync_bookmarks::BookmarkModelObserverImpl, and analogous concepts are

planned to be introduced in future patches.



The patch is mostly mechanical as most observers either didn't use the

parameter or should trivially switch to something else. The few

exceptions with less trivial changes include:

1. BookmarkUndoService, which temporarily (and until the migration

work that motivates this patch is completed) observes multiple

BookmarkModel instances.

2. The iOS version of HistoryClientImpl, which now issues more lookups

to determine whether a URL has, in fact, been un-bookmarked (instead

of smartly issuing the lookup in the "other" BookmarkModel instance).

These two lookups will also go away once the very same migration

is completed.

entry.title: Split out StyledStrokeData from StrokeData
entry.content:
Add a new StyledStrokeData class that represent the bits of StrokeData

that are needed to describe a stroke based StrokeStyle. This involves

moving out the code that translates the specified stroke style to a

"full" set of stroke data. Add a GeometryInfo struct for forwarding the

description of the shape to be drawn with the stroke.



Remove unused stroke-related setters from GraphicsContext. Code that

draws "advanced" strokes already make use of StrokeData directly, and

thus nothing sets anything but stroke style and thickness.

The SetLineCap() in BoxBorderPainter::DrawWideDottedBoxSideFromPath() is

redundant, because the cap will be resolved to "round" on the resulting

PaintFlags since the style is "dotted".



Clean up GraphicsContextTest.UnboundedDrawsAreClipped. This test sets a

entry.content:
This CL adds:



* A GetTextureTarget() variant that computes the BufferFormat from the

ClientSI's format rather than having it passed in. This will make

upcoming changes more ergonomic (otherwise they would need to get the

format *out* of the ClientSharedImage and convert it to a BufferFormat

only to pass it back into the ClientSharedImage).

texture target differently based on whether this SharedImage is an

overlay candidate (in the fullness of time, ClientSharedImage will
